Frankfurt parking fees are to rise sharply
Parking in Frankfurt could soon be significantly more expensive.
The magistrate of the city this morning advises on a template of traffic Councillor Stefan Majer (Green).
Accordingly, the parking fees are to be increased by 50 percent.
But that are not raised prices, but the time interval from parking meters and ticket machines to be reduced from 30 to 20 minutes.
In December must then decide nor the city council.
The Retail Committee of the Frankfurt Chamber of Commerce holds the "not a good idea."
The parking directly outside the shop was "a not to be underestimated advantage for smaller retailers."
The Traffic Club Germany is of the opinion that an increase after two decades "entirely appropriate and actually long overdue" is.
Public transport will also be more expensive.
